Police minister Bheki Cele says the police are aware of a plot to kill members of a task team investigating political killings in KwaZulu-Natal. Cele said this at the memorial service of African National Congress (ANC) activist Martin Sithole, who was gunned down in northern KwaZulu-Natal. Buthanani Shange, a bystander, was also killed. Cele also said a suspect in the case will be behind bars on Monday. It was an emotional farewell for Sithole, attended by hundreds of friends and family and ANC members. #sabcnews #sabckzn Life of an ANC activist in Newcastle Martin Sithole is being remembered by his fellow comrades and his family. He was shot and killed last Sunday by unknown men, he died along with his friend Buthanani Shange. pic.twitter.com/aXDJOrE7JF — Nonkululeko Hlophe (@Leko3) May 16, 2019 WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: 